{
  "text": "A retrospective, full PRNP open reading frame genotyping was conducted at the end of the studies and some Suffolk sheep (Table 1) were found to be MT or TT at codon 112 of PRNP (M, methionine and T threonine); they were not considered in the calculations of ARs and STs in view of the reported resistance of such sheep to oral BSE [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
